OL,3,CFrom the newsroom to the farm: A
OL,4,Cweekend lambing in Somerset
OL,6,FIdeally the ewe will do it all
OL,7,Fthemselves, but sometimes you do need
OL,8,Fto step in and help.
OL,10,FThe lamb should be coming with its
OL,11,Ffront legs and head first, but
OL,12,Fsometimes they could be presenting
OL,13,Fdifferently (tangled up with a
OL,14,Fsibling, leg or head back, coming
OL,15,Fbackwards) so you need to help the ewe.
OL,17,FOnce the lamb is born the ewe will
OL,18,Flick it dry, and within minutes the
OL,19,Flambs are on their feet.
